ğŸš€ SQL Fundamentals â€“ SELECT, WHERE, GROUP BY, ORDER BY

These are the basic SQL commands used to retrieve and organize data in a relational database. Letâ€™s break them down with examples and hands-on exercises.
1ï¸âƒ£ SELECT â€“ Retrieving Data

The SELECT statement is used to retrieve data from a database table.
ğŸ“ Syntax:

SELECT column1, column2 FROM table_name;

âœ… Example:

Retrieve all customer names and their emails from the Customers table.

SELECT customer_name, email FROM Customers;

ğŸ”¹ * selects all columns from the table:

